    "markdown_debrief": "### \ud83e\ude7a Surgical Board Practice Item\n\n**Metadata:** HPB | Vascular Anatomy | Liver Blood Supply\n**Target Level:** Resident\n\n**\ud83d\udcdd The Clinical Vignette**\nWhich of the following statements is true about the blood supply to the liver?\n\n* A) The portal vein provides 75% of the blood supply to the liver\n* B) The hepatic artery provides 75% of the blood supply to the liver\n* C) Blood supply to the intrahepatic bile ducts is mainly through the portal vein\n* D) The portal vein provides 50% of the blood supply to the liver\n\n**Correct Answer:** A) The portal vein provides 75% of the blood supply to the liver\n\n---\n\n### \u26a1 SHARP 4.0 Cognitive & Surgical Debrief\n\n**\ud83d\udccc S \u2013 Set the Stage (The Verdict & Diagnostic Pivot)**\n* **The Verdict:** Correct: A.  The portal vein is the dominant supplier.\n* **The Diagnostic Pivot:** The relative contribution of the hepatic artery versus the portal vein is a key differentiator in understanding liver physiology and pathology, particularly in the context of HPB surgery.\n\n**\ud83c\udfaf H \u2013 Highlight Excellence (The Surgical \u201cWhy\u201d & Pathology)**\n* **Surgical Mechanism:** The liver\u2019s dual blood supply \u2013 primarily portal venous and secondarily hepatic arterial \u2013 is crucial for its metabolic function. The portal vein delivers nutrient-rich blood from the digestive system, while the hepatic artery provides oxygenated blood.\n* **Clinical Execution:** Understanding this distribution is vital for predicting hepatic ischemia, managing post-operative bleeding, and appreciating the impact of vascular interventions.\n* **\ud83d\udc41\ufe0f Mental Operative Theatre:**  Imagine a surgeon meticulously dissecting around the hepatic artery, recognizing that its contribution, while important, is significantly less than the massive flow of the portal vein.  The surgeon anticipates potential bleeding points along the portal vein tributaries.\n\n**\u274c A \u2013 Address the Gaps (Systematic Distractor Demolition)**\n* **Option B (Incorrect):** The hepatic artery provides approximately 25% of the liver\u2019s blood supply.  It\u2019s crucial for oxygenating the hepatocytes, but the portal vein dominates.\n* **Option C (Incorrect):** While the portal vein does supply the intrahepatic bile ducts, it\u2019s not *mainly* through it. The bile ducts receive blood from branches of the hepatic artery and portal vein.\n* **Option D (Incorrect):** The portal vein provides approximately 75% of the liver\u2019s blood supply.  This is a fundamental anatomical fact.\n\n**\ud83d\udcca R \u2013 Review Learning Points (Evidence-Based Framework)**\n| **Classification / System / Criteria** | **Key Diagnostic / Imaging Finding** | **Immediate Surgical / Clinical Pivot** | **Core Guideline / Surgical Society Consensus** |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Grade A \u2013 Anatomy** | Hepatic Artery/Portal Vein Ratio (75/25) | Selective hepatic artery ligation during HPB surgery. | SAGES, ASCRS, ATLS |\n| **Grade B \u2013 Physiology** | Portal Hypertension & Increased Portal Venous Pressure |  Management of portal hypertension (e.g., shunt placement) | NCCN |\n\n**\u26a0\ufe0f Critical Guideline Updates & Textbook Conflicts**\n* **Standard Textbooks (Bailey & Love / Sabiston / Schwartz):** All consistently state the 75/25 ratio of portal/hepatic venous supply.\n* **Society Guidelines (ATLS / SAGES / NCCN / EAES):**  Reinforce the importance of understanding this ratio for surgical planning and management.\n* **The Discrepancy:** None. This is a foundational anatomical concept.\n\n**\ud83d\udca1 P \u2013 Plan for Improvement (The Exam Heuristic)**\n* **The Board Pearl:** \u201cRemember the 75/25 \u2013 Portal vein dominates, hepatic artery supports.\u201d  Quickly recall this ratio when assessing liver blood supply."
